Charles Graeber is an award-winning journalist and New York Times bestselling author of THE GOOD NURSE: A True Story of Medicine, Madness, and Murder (published by Twelve). 

He is also a contributor to numerous publications including Wired, GQ, The New Yorker, New York Magazine, Vogue, Outside Magazine, MenÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s Journal, Bloomberg Businessweek, Travel + Leisure, and The New York Times, and an occasional guest on CNN, NPR, and other radio programs. His work has been honored with the Overseas Press Club award for outstanding international journalism, the New York Press Club prize for the yearÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s best magazine spot news reportage, several National Magazine Award-nominations, and inclusion in numerous anthologies including The Best American Crime Writing, The Best American Science Writing, The Best American Business Writing and The Best of National Geographic Adventure. 

Born in Iowa, he now lives in Nantucket, MA and Brooklyn, NY.




